<br>
None of their existing spells operate like this. New code is the deevil.<br>
<br>
33% is too much for a rank 1 to 3 spell. I wouldn't start it at level 1, anyways. It's not needed there. Having it percentage based makes it very exploitable. It should probably be a set amount.<br>
<br>
The spells should follow the existing level format.<br>
<br>
Having it proc every hit is probably too much. If it operated like a normal proc (with a percentage chance to hit), it would be better.<br>
<br>
This would be a better progression:<br>
<br>
Infusion of Ro/E'ci/Thunder<br>
Level 20/24/29<br>
Chance of +16 fire/+16 cold/+24 magic damage<br>
<br>
Saturation of Ro/E'ci/Thunder<br>
Level 34/39/44<br>
Chance of +48 fire/+48 cold/+64 magic damage<br>
<br>
Embodiment of Ro/E'ci/Thunder<br>
Level 60/62/64<br>
Chance of +128 fire/+128 cold/+196 magic damage<br>
<br>
Mana, casting time, etc... based on level of spell.<br>
<br>
Overall, I don't think we need it. And we're not buffers.<br>
<br>
